2011-03-12T18:20:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/south-africa-wins-by-3-wickets-to-hand-india-first-cricket-world-cup-loss.html
  South Africa  handed  India  its first
loss at the Cricket World Cup, winning by three wickets in
Nagpur.  India, led by Sachin Tendulkarâ€™s 111, reached 267-1 before
losing its final nine wickets in nine overs to be bowled out for
296. Dale Steyn took 5-50 for the visitors.  Jacques Kallis (69), Hasim Amla (61) and AB de Villiers
(52) helped South Africa reach its target of 297 with two balls
reamining. Robin Peterson scored 16 runs off the first four
balls of the final over as Proteas finished 300-7.  India remains atop Group B with seven points from five
games, followed by West Indies and South Africa, who have six
points each from one fewer game. The top four teams in the two
seven-team groups advance to the quarterfinals.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
